SAPS&#8217; Ethekwini Inner South Cluster team has recovered R500 000 of counterfeit South African currency, two printers and different bottles of ink used to produce the fake notes from a home in Montclair, south of Durban, KwaZulu-Natal police said on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Priya Nunkumar said a suspect was arrested and would appear in court soon. ALSO READ: Suspended KZN top cop s case postponed Ethekwini Inner South Cluster Commander Major-General Keerath Nunkumar commended members for apprehending the suspect. We will have a zero-tolerance approach on counterfeit money which is widely circulated in our community. All businesses and members of the community must be cautious when accepting money. African News Agency (ANA)